{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, it has recently been argued that AI contributes to the perpetuation of speciesist bias [10] and that it may further increase animal suffering in factory farming [11].",
    "A full examination of catastrophic AI risks would need to examine whether AI poses catastrophic risks to non-human animals, and -if so -what to do about them.",
    "Second, some researchers have argued that future AI might be sentient, and thus capable of suffering [12][13][14].",
    "Since AI systems can be copied easily, the possibility of AI suffering would arguably quickly lead to astronomically high suffering and thus a moral catastrophe.",
    "3 1 For instance, human or non-human suffering on a massive scale might also count as a catastrophe in this sense."
  ]
}